race.comment: INQUISITOR (5) led over 1200m at Murwillumbah last start but couldn't maintain the pressure and was swamped close to home. Has raced here at this distance once for a win. Sure to give them something to catch with a bit less pressure on today over the longer journey. FLYING ARGENTO (1) has transferred from Gary Portelli to Ben Hull and is back after a break of three months. Has never fired when fresh but this looks a softer first-up assignment than usual. Can bob up without surprising. CALL OUT (3) returned with a solid effort in a Warwick Class 3 last start. Down in grade and has won second-up before so this is not out of reach. MISHANI SUSPECT (6) won here last start over 1265m when second-up from a spell. Not a prolific winner so might struggle to repeat that effort, but worth throwing in the exotics. EXPLOSIVE POWER (2) can improve second-up over a bit more ground.
